1580
01:34:16.894 --> 01:34:20.634
So together, our data has formed this model where in the

1581
01:34:20.774 --> 01:34:24.534
low SYN cells, GTOX inhibitor may induce DNA

1582
01:34:24.574 --> 01:34:28.534
damage, but they can be resolved. So the cells can escape the

1583
01:34:28.574 --> 01:34:31.934
aura kinase A arrest by slippage or division.

1584
01:34:32.794 --> 01:34:36.734
And for the SYN high cells, however, the GTOX inhibitor

1585
01:34:36.794 --> 01:34:40.374
cause mitotic DNA damage which cannot be resolved,

1586
01:34:40.754 --> 01:34:44.654
and that will track into the mitosis, activate

1587
01:34:44.974 --> 01:34:48.794
ATM, ATR, and cause cyclin B1 stabilization

1588
01:34:48.864 --> 01:34:50.174
and mitotic catastrophe.

1589
01:34:51.374 --> 01:34:52.334
And hopefully our

1590
01:34:53.674 --> 01:34:57.444
study can show that GTOX inhibitor-induced

1591
